Any free elective can go here. A maximum of 10 units of elective credit may be required for the major to reach the 180 unit requirement to graduate. Excess units of AP Test credit may be applied to elective credit. The Chemistry Department strongly recommended taking CHEM 101 (1) in your first quarter. Also, it is suggested that you take supplemental workshops (SCM 150) along with available Math/Science courses in your first year.
